<collectingCountry box="[404,497,850,873]" name="Mexico" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="88.[124,654,193,993]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" box="[603,653,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akis">
<emphasis box="[603,653,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">akis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(point) is a Greek noun. I wish to accentuate the testaceous coloration of the antennal apex.
</paragraph>
